  {
    "number": 81,
    "question": "Are all true believers at all times assured of their present being in the estate of",
    "answer": "grace, and that they shall be saved? A. Assurance of grace and salvation not being of the essence of faith, true believers may wait long before they obtain it; and, after the enjoyment thereof, may have it weakened and intermitted, through manifold distempers, sins, temptations, and desertions; yet they are never left without such a presence and support of the Spirit of God as keeps them from sinking into utter despair.",
    "clauses": [
      {
        "text": "grace, and that they shall be saved? A. Assurance of grace and salvation not being of the essence of faith,",
